      "content": "i hear that, but isn't it kind of a stretch to say that teaching these things helps \"reduce\" divisiveness when so many parents and politicians are actually fighting about it right now? feels like the curriculum itself is becoming one of the things causing the tension. wouldn't it be more neutral to just stick to the traditional facts rather than trying to teach empathy through certain perspectives?",
